  "texts": [
    "Consequently, the research community is gradually shifting towards execution-based metrics, such as compilation success rate, test pass rate, and executability [79].",
    "Therefore, we strongly advocate that future research should prioritize runtime metrics (e.g., code coverage, mutation score, bug detection rate) as the primary measure of effectiveness.",
    "To address the benchmark issue, recent efforts have focused on creating domain-oriented benchmarks, such as CPP-UT-Bench [17], TestGenEval [70], and TestEval for line/branch/path coverage targets [141].",
    "These benchmarks are specifically designed for LLMs and carefully curated to avoid training data contamination.",
    "Similarly, to systematically evaluate model capabilities in long-context and coverage-oriented generation, new benchmarks like CLOVER have been proposed, which construct high-quality oracle contexts through coverage analysis to provide more challenging scenarios for model evaluation [146].High Cost and Low Efficiency."
